reviews.review_text: Greatest Big River of all time Incredible!!

Yeah, not half bad... Actually, played with Gusto! (or is that Gusteaux)
But I was thinking there are some weak parts, and when one attempts to stand the whole show up against the rest of that two week stretch, from Spectrum (hell even Boston Music Hall) through Stanley Theater, it feels like it might actually be the weakest of this legendary period! 
I take special interest in these two shows, though it was always hard to get decent recordings. I grew up in that no horse town... oh wait, there's a horse on a fountain right in the middle of town... I don't recall if there's a rider mounted on it... I seem to vaguely recall through the haze of this perforated memory there is no rider!
There is Know Rider! anyway...
